node.text: Kings & Queens of Corbet’s returns for the fourth year with all lady competitors launching off the nose of Corbet’s during the first run for the first time ever. Conditions were tough and putting it to their feet was difficult so strategies shifted in run 2 to putting down a clean top to bottom run without any bobbles. Style and fluidity prevailed at the athlete judging. Watch @madmads.world, @audreysnowclimb and @zoefloweee take the top three spots in this year's competition. Link in bio to see all the ladies send it into Corbet’s Couloir check out the full competition on Red Bull TV. #jacksonhole #jhdreaming

node.title: Kings & Queens of Corbet’s Top 3 Women

At the end of the day, the masses of skiers and riders head to après while a new shift of workers clock in. This dedicated group of employees work tirelessly through the night in preparation for the sun to rise and the first chair to load. Wind, snow and sweat have built a history that has stretched over a half century - with a simple common denominator being the storylines we leave in the snow. 

All footage filmed Winter 2019.20. Face coverings are required this winter for all staff and guests.

Join JHMR employees as they welcome the coming winter.

node.text: Born and raised in Jackson, WY Kira Brazinski, @yogikira, has found a great love for the outdoors. Her lifestyle involves hiking, skiing, biking and pursuing her career as a yoga instructor. Kira was born with a rare birth defect resulting in missing most of her left leg. Since being able to walk, she has used a prosthetic leg. While some might see this as a major setback, Kira's fiery passion and athleticism drives her to achieve her goals and amaze those around her with her achievements. Climbing the iconic Grand Teton has been a childhood dream of Kira's. In A Grand Journey short documentary film we get an intimate look into Kira’s unique but incredibly relatable journey as she attempts to take on a goal she herself may not believe is possible.
